Akmal ran through easy from the non-striker's end to steal the strike, but Bravo, whose weight was on the back foot, was late starting, and the keeper flung the ball to the bowler, who threw down the stumps at the non-striker's end to run him out

Rumman Raees to Umar Akmal, SIX, shot! What a hit to end the innings! It's very full outside off, but Akmal was prepared for that. Steps back, deep into his crease, and creates a bit of leverage to simply whip it away, high over midwicket
